{"id":19456,"title":"Streptococcus suis-related prosthetic joint infection and streptococcal toxic shock-like syndrome in a pig farmer in the United States.","abstract":"Streptococcus suis is an emerging swine-associated zoonotic agent that can cause meningitis and septicemia in humans. We present, to our knowledge, the first case of S. suis arthroplasty infection and streptococcal toxic shock-like syndrome due to an nonencapsulated serotype 5 strain in North America. ","date":"2014-05-23","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24719433","annotations":[{"name":"Sepsis","weight":0.877753,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sepsis"},{"name":"Meningitis","weight":0.847996,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meningitis"},{"name":"United States","weight":0.748062,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.740234,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Pig","weight":0.650591,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pig"},{"name":"North America","weight":0.607696,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_America"},{"name":"Joint","weight":0.56771,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joint"},{"name":"Human","weight":0.46934,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human"},{"name":"Zoonosis","weight":0.354949,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zoonosis"},{"name":"Syndrome","weight":0.307909,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syndrome"},{"name":"Serotype","weight":0.294048,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serotype"},{"name":"Septic arthritis","weight":0.290379,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Septic_arthritis"},{"name":"Strain (biology)","weight":0.290163,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strain_(biology)"},{"name":"Toxicity","weight":0.159972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wi